                <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="48" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL" onselect="storeCaret(this);" onclick="storeCaret(this);" onkeyup="storeCaret(this);" onchange="storeCaret(this);">[quote][i]Originally posted by Darkmatil[/i]
[br]If you are lvl 60+ and looking for some nice exp and willing to take some risks try the Arachnae Defilers in the very back of the zone.  You follow left wall all the way back until it turns to the right, keep going until it turns again past the cave and you run into the defilers.  They HT for 900, hit for about 400-500 and can use boiling blood and darkness on you.  Since there are so many of them here the best tactic is to root dot.  Here is what I did:

-epic snare (or darkness).  Do this to one that's not near the others.  If it resists try to root it quick (you must have a lot of HP in case it gets to you before you can root it)
-Root with paralyzing earth.
-Stack Pyro, Dark plague or splurt, FP if you have it.  Vexing.
-Don't bother to wait for epic snare or darkness to wear off, snare again when you think it's almost time for it to break.

At 61 I got about 4% AA exp from these each kill.  Doesn't take that long to kill.  They can drop parchments, but it's really rare.

[center][img]http://home.attbi.com/~cmolstad/darksig.jpg[/img][/center][center][b][url="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=360370"]Darkmatil Bonebringer[/url][/b][/center][center]61st level Warlock from Brell Serilis[/center][center][url="http://www.sarcastic.org/AoD/yabbse/"]Aftermath of Darkness[/url][/center]
[/quote]</textarea><br /></td>
